-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--  §5.  Orbit Coherence
-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
--  The coarse-graining witness carries a  compat  field that
--  witnesses the factorization:
--
--    S-cut d100BdyView r ≡ S-cut-rep (classify100 r)
--
--  This holds by refl because S-cut is DEFINED as
--  S-cut-rep ∘ classify100 in Boundary/Dense100Cut.agda.
--
--  The area-law bound factors through this:
--
--    S-cut d100BdyView r  ≤ℚ  regionArea r
--    ‖ (by compat)
--    S-cut-rep (classify100 r)  ≤ℚ  regionArea r
--
--  An observer who sees only the 8-constructor D100OrbitRep type
--  reads the correct entropy value for each orbit class (via
--  S-cut-rep), and the area law holds for every region in the
--  orbit (via area-law).  This is the type-theoretic content of
--  "statistical averaging preserves the entropy–area relationship."
-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- The compat field is refl (S-cut is S-cut-rep ∘ classify100)
compat-is-trivial : (r : D100Region)
  → S-cut d100BdyView r ≡ S-cut-rep (classify100 r)
compat-is-trivial = CoarseGrainWitness.compat the-witness


